sentences: Christina Pluhar (Graz, 1965) is an Austrian theorbist, harpist, conductor, and director of L'Arpeggiata ensemble.
In 1992, as a member of the Ensemble La Fenice, she received the first prize at the Festival of Early Music in Malmö.
With her ensemble L'Arpeggiata, founded in 2000, she plays at international festivals and makes recordings.

In addition to her activities as a musician and ensemble director, Christina Pluhar has been teaching baroque harp at the Royal Conservatory of The Hague since 1999 and gives master classes at the University of Graz.
